      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-400">The <strong>Great Wave off Kanagawa tattoo</strong> is one of the most requested Japanese-inspired designs — and for good reason. At its core it symbolizes <strong>resilience, respect for nature's power, and overcoming adversity</strong>. Whether you call it a <em>Kanagawa tattoo</em> or a <em>Hokusai wave tattoo</em>, the meaning connects a 200-year-old woodblock print to a very personal story.</p>
